### 1. Register a new user
POST http://localhost:5000/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fullName": "Test User",
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "phone": "0123456789"
}

### 2. Login (Copy the accessToken from the response)
# @name login
POST http://localhost:5000/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 3. Get Public Movies (No token needed)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/movies

### 4. Try to access Admin Route without Token (Should fail 401/403)
GET http://localhost:5000/admin/movies

### 5. Try to access Admin Route WITH Token (Might fail if role is 'customer')
# Replace <ACCESS_TOKEN> with the token from the login response
GET http://localhost:5000/admin/movies
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.accessToken}}

### 6. (Admin Only) Create a Movie
POST http://localhost:5000/admin/movies
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "New Movie created by Admin",
  "description": "Description",
  "director": "Director Name",
  "duration": 120,
  "releaseDate": "2025-01-01",
  "posterUrl": "http://example.com/poster.jpg",
  "trailerUrl": "http://example.com/trailer.mp4"
}
